  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 106 g
  sugar: 46 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 850 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/smokehouse-pulled-chicken-bowls-5f5fa43ab7994b69f050a7e4
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}. Drain @Corn{13.4%ounce}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly slice half the @Jalapeño{1}; mince remaining.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, a small squeeze of lime juice, and a small pinch of lime zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and @Pepper{}.

In a second small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, juice from half the lime, @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), a splash of water, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{1%minute}. Let stand until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over high heat. Add corn and as much minced jalapeño as you like. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Reduce heat to low; stir in @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4). (You'll use the rest of the spice blend in the next step.) Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @BBQ Pulled Chicken{10%ounce}, remaining @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}, and juice from remaining lime. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, ~{1-2%minutes}, or until chicken is warmed through (165 degrees).

> Stir in a splash of water if mixture seems dry.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in remaining lime zest and @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}; top with pulled chicken and corn. Garnish with lime crema, some pickled shallot (draining first), and as much sliced jalapeño as you like. Serve.